post_text: Now that the sport season is here, I wanted to let you know on the new spectator rules. Unfortunately, due to gym capacity rules, each athlete will be given 1 or 2 vouchers (depending on gym size) to give to their parents or grandparents to be able to enter the gym. These vouchers are only meant for immediate family. Unfortunately, no students will be able to attend games at this time. In a perfect scenario, this is short term. I know this will be tough for many people as they enjoy watching our athletes play even though they might not be related. As soon as things open up, we will allow more in the gym but at this time, all schools will be following this protocol.

post_text:
Please come out to the girls game tonight here to honor the lives of two of our students who passed away unexpectedly yesterday. We also are sending all of our strength and love to another one who is in the Green Bay hospital. Our kids need to feel the support of each other and this community more than we know during this difficult time. The students ask that you please wear your best “Yooper” outfit to honor the boys.
This game is also Parents' Night for senior girls basketball players and band members. Parents' Night recognition will occur following the JV game. A moment of silence and dedication to Dylan, Christopher and Hunter organized by some of our students will occur prior to the Varsity game. Donations to the families will be accepted in lieu of paying admission to the game.
